{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"afdba06d-98f1-4856-9d16-444e09c77fca","content":"The change is straightforward. In your project file, remove (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Remove this line (or set to false): -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**What this does:**\n\n- `MSTest.Sdk` 3.8+ uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. Setting `UseVSTest` to `true` was opting you back into the legacy runner.\n- Simply removing that property switches you to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\n**Other things to check:**\n\n1. **Run tests via CLI** — use `dotnet test` as usual; it works with both runners.\n2. **Custom `.runsettings`** — most settings carry over, but review for VSTest-specific nodes.\n3. **`dotnet test` output** — you'll now see the new test output format (per-test-host process).\n4. **CI pipelines** — if you pass `-- RunConfiguration.*` style args, verify they're still supported.\n5. **Extensions** — replace any `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestPlatform.*` package references with their `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` equivalents if applicable.\n\nNo additional NuGet packages are required; the SDK handles it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"17b2ac76-3f22-4c03-b556-c98dcff266ed","outputTokens":339,"requestId":"2869:2EE1E2:1655D67:17BAAD8:6A045FD0"},"id":"275cb0e8-aa35-4292-a878-49de87877985","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:26:18.582Z","parentId":"833ea166-6be5-4ae0-a889-2af6252d35ec"}
